headline.main: VARGAS ADOPTED 'STRONG MAN' ROLE; Held Power Longer Than Any Other Brazilian President -- Popular With the People

snippet: Getulio Vargas retained a strong grip on the imagination and affection of many Brazilians. Sometimes he was known by his nickname, "Ge-Ge" and again, when he appeared in public, his followers would greet him with a chanting shout, "Getul, Getul!"
